Description: Maximum likelihood estimation for parameterized conductance models
  via Newton and quasi-Newton methods, for moderate-sized problems
  such as spatial grids with fewer than a million cells. Supports
  terra-native workflows, multiple measurement models, spline and scale-aware
  conductance estimation, cross-validation across supported conductance
  models, and selected-pair analysis while retaining all focal sites in the
  resistance graph.
